Description: Pedestrian bridge intended for crossing an infrastructure.
Isolated bridge, not connected to a communication route.

A structure generally parallel to the coast, designed to protect the coast or shoreline from flooding of the land beyond. A dike is watertight and separates areas of different elevations. It is not intended for the berthing of ships.

A quay or section of a quay where ships dock to load or unload passengers (regular or tourist transport, maritime or river), not goods (see Quay). In practice, it must be the departure point for a regular or tourist maritime service.
A rigid structure built, extending into the sea, a lake or a river.
A structure, most often built on stilts or floating, allowing the berthing of small pleasure boats or fishing vessels.
